Statements:
[
    "An angular unconformity reflects a tectonic event involving significant deformation and uplift.",
    "Followed by erosion and subsequent sediment deposition.",
    "This geological feature indicates a period of tectonic activity that tilted or folded older rock layers.",
    "Which were then eroded.",
    "After this erosion, new sedimentary layers were deposited horizontally on top of the eroded surface.",
    "The angular discordance between the older, tilted layers and the newer, horizontal layers is indicative of past tectonic movements.",
    "Such as mountain building (orogeny) or other crustal deformations.",
    "Followed by a period of relative tectonic stability allowing for sedimentation."
] 

